                <list>
                  <item xml:id = "a1">
                    <desc>
                    </desc>
                    <locus from = "#ir" to = "#iir"/> Asmat prayer of Jeremiah against the evil eye, with incipit <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዓይን፡ ወዓይነት፡..</foreign> (<title ref = "EMIP00009"/>, f. IIIrv (varia)
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target = "#47r"/> Psalm 60:9
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a3">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target = "#63v"/> Marginal symbol and note at Psalm 78:14 indicating the point “half” of the way through the Psalms
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target = "#63v"/> An ornate symbol and the word “half” mark the midpoint of the Psalms
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a5">
                    <desc>
                      Copied by <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ሣህለ፡ እግዚእ፡</foreign>, <locus target = "#150v #166v"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id = "a6">
                      <desc>
                        Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#9v #15v #33v #70v #99r #134v"/>);
                        and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#52r #80v #88v #102r #117v #126r #132v"/>);
                        and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target = "#18r"/>, line 5),
                        and in another case where the symbol (+) is used (<locus target = "#123v"/>, line 10, <locus target = "#145v"/>, line 6).
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id = "e1">
                      <desc>
                        Open space left for potential <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> <locus from = "#115v"/>
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id = "e2">
                      <desc>
                        <locus from = "#iiv" to = "#iiir"/>, <locus from = "#168v" to = "#169v"/> blank
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id = "e3">
                      <desc>
                        The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                        Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an
                        appropriate script size. On some occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the line
                        with words written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., <locus target = "#8v #9v #48v #96r"/>).
                        Other times, a line is too long and has to be completed above (e.g., <locus target = "#2v #4v #5v #6r #7r #7v"/>, etc.) or
                        below (e.g., <locus target = "#35r #45v #51v #149v"/>) the end of the line
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
